<% content_for(:html_title) { "Clocktower Companion Privacy Policy" } %>
<div id="privacy-policy-body">

    <div class="bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-800 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-100 h-screen leading-normal">
        <div id="dark-mode-controls">
            <div class="w-10 absolute top-5 right-36">
            <label class="relative flex justify-between items-center group p-2 text-xl">
                Dark Mode
                <input id="dark-mode-toggle" type="checkbox" checked class="absolute left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-full h-full peer hidden rounded-md" />
                <span class="w-16 h-10 flex items-center flex-shrink-0 ml-4 p-1 bg-gray-400 rounded-full duration-300 ease-in-out peer-checked:bg-green-400 after:w-8 after:h-8 after:bg-white after:rounded-full after:shadow-md after:duration-300 peer-checked:after:translate-x-6 group-hover:after:translate-x-1"></span>
            </label>
        </div>

        <div class="p-10 leading-8">
            <div class="mb-4">
                <p class="text-4xl mb-10">Privacy Policy</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base mb-4">Your privacy is important to us. It is our policy to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect from you using our extension, Clocktower Companion.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">We only collect very basic information about your use of the extension that are necessary to provide you with your requested service.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">We only retain collected information for as long as necessary to provide you with your requested service. What data we store, we'll protect within commercially acceptable means to prevent loss and theft, as well as unauthorized access, disclosure, copying, use or modification.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">We don't share any personally identifying information publicly or with third-parties, except when required to by law.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">Our extension may link to external sites that are not operated by us. Please be aware that we have no control over the content and practices of these sites, and cannot accept responsibility or liability for their respective privacy policies.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">You are free to refuse our request for your personal information, with the understanding that we may be unable to provide you with some of your desired services.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">Your installing and activation of our extension will be regarded as acceptance of our practices around privacy and personal information. If you have any questions about how we handle user data and personal information, feel free to contact us.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">If you'd like to review, remove, export, restrict processing of your data, contact us at provided contact email.</p>

            <div class="mb-4">
                <p class="text-3xl">What Data is Collected</p>
            </div>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">The usage of our extension is logged. The only personally identifiable pieces of information stored in the logs are the player names on the Grimoire. 
                Apart from that, only information about usage of our extension is stored for debugging purposes and for analyzing traffic.</p>

            <p class="text-base mb-4">This policy is effective as of April 1st, 2022.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    const body = document.querySelector("#privacy-policy-body");
    const checkbox = document.querySelector("#dark-mode-toggle");

    const toggleDarkMode = () => {
        console.log("toggle", checkbox.checked)
        if(checkbox.checked) {
            body.classList.add("dark");
        } else {
            body.classList.remove("dark");
        }
    }
    toggleDarkMode();
    checkbox.addEventListener("click", toggleDarkMode);
</script>